export const skillDocs = "---\nname: generate-elementor-page-custom-css\ndescription: Generate a ready-to-import Elementor V4 template JSON for a page, section, or portion of a page from a user goal, styling exclusively via variant-level custom_css (base64-encoded CSS declarations in styles[].variants[].custom_css.raw) \u2014 no typed style PropValues and no styles-schema discovery. Use when the user wants V4 atomic output like generate-elementor-page but with raw CSS in custom_css instead of Style_Schema props, global classes, global variables, or companion JSON. Triggers: same as generate-elementor-page (build/generate/create page, hero, landing, section, e-flexbox tree) plus mentions of custom_css, raw CSS styling, or avoiding global classes/variables.\n---\n\n# Generate Elementor V4 Page (custom_css)\n\n## One-shot execution path (default \u2014 use this unless told otherwise)\n\nOne-shot from a screenshot, URL, or description follows exactly **seven** steps. **Do not emit Elementor JSON** until **Step 5** (convert draft \u2192 schema): that requires **Step 3** (`HTML_DRAFT` + `CSS_DRAFT`) complete and **Step 4** satisfied (user approval **or** the brief explicitly says \"go ahead\" / \"skip approval\" / equivalent).\n\n**Step 0 \u2014 Discovery (mandatory; emit `DISCOVERY` before the brief)**\n\nFor each discovery topic, walk this source-resolution order and stop at the first hit:\n\n1. MCP `elementor://...` resource, when `user-elementor-mcp-server` is healthy and exposes the URI.\n2. Workspace dump at `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page-custom-css/discovery/<topic>.json`.\n3. wp-env probe via `validator/` or `import.sh` if a future hook exists.\n4. Skill-baked default documented here or in `reference.md`.\n\nIf nothing hits, use the default and add the topic to `discovery_gaps`.\n\nDiscovery topics:\n\n- `context/general` \u2192 `{ pro_active: bool, elementor_version: str, postId: number|null }`. Default: `{ pro_active: false, elementor_version: \"0.4\", postId: null }`.\n- `widgets/available` \u2192 list of `{ type, version, is_container }`. Default: `e-flexbox`, `e-div-block`, `e-heading`, `e-paragraph`, `e-button`, `e-image`, `e-tabs`, `e-tab`, `e-tabs-menu`, `e-tabs-content-area`, `e-tab-content`, `e-svg`, `e-divider`, `e-youtube`. Do not emit a widget tag not in this list.\n- `widgets/schema/{type}` \u2192 per-widget **settings** schema + `llm_guidance`. Default: the canonical content-key table below.\n- `breakpoints/list` \u2192 list of enabled breakpoint ids. Default: `[desktop, tablet, mobile]`.\n- `interactions/schema` \u2192 only fetched when the brief calls for interactions. Default: free-tier subset from `reference.md`.\n- `design_guidelines` \u2192 read `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page-custom-css/design-guidelines.md` first; if missing, read `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/design-guidelines.md`; if both missing, read `design-guidelines.md` at the workspace root; if all missing, rely on the brief.\n\n**Not used by this skill (do not fetch or emit):** `styles/schema/{category}`, `global-variables`, `global-classes`, companion payloads, `DESIGN_SYSTEM.catalog`, or typed style `props` beyond `{}`.\n\n**Step 1 \u2014 Extract brief (mandatory; output these lines before Step 3 `HTML_DRAFT`)**\n\n```\nREFERENCE_TYPE: screenshot | url | description\nLOCALE: he-IL+RTL | en-US+LTR | \u2026\nPAGE_TYPE: ecommerce-home | landing | section-only | other:<name>\nSECTIONS: [ordered list, max 8, one line each]\nMUST_HAVE_WIDGETS: [e-image, e-button, e-heading, \u2026]\nAPPROXIMATE_COUNTS: { category_icons: 16, promo_tiles_row1: 6, \u2026 }\nOUTPUT_TARGET: db-inject (default) | template-import\nDESIGN_GUIDELINES: inline | <path> | none\n```\n\nDefault: `OUTPUT_TARGET: db-inject` unless the user explicitly says \"template import\".\n\nBrand colors, fonts, and spacing still come from the brief and `design-guidelines.md` \u2014 encode them **inside** `custom_css` CSS strings (hex literals, `font-family`, etc.). There is no separate `BRAND_COLORS:` line requirement.\n\nEmit `DISCOVERY` before `HTML_DRAFT` (shape in `reference.md`). Example no-source block:\n\n```yaml\nDISCOVERY:\n  source_resolution: { all: default }\n  pro_active: false\n  elementor_version: \"0.4\"\n  breakpoints: [desktop, tablet, mobile]\n  widgets_available: [e-flexbox, e-div-block, e-heading, e-paragraph, e-button, e-image, e-tabs, ...]\n  design_guidelines_source: .cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page-custom-css/design-guidelines.md\n  discovery_gaps: [context/general, widgets/available, breakpoints/list]\n```\n\n**When `REFERENCE_TYPE: description`:** Ask for a screenshot or URL before proceeding **unless** they said to go ahead. Supply thematic Unsplash URLs for every `e-image`. Do not leave `url` empty.\n\n**Step 2 \u2014 Select PAGE_TYPE playbook** (see \"Page-type playbooks\") and confirm section order. Apply creativity gates from \"Design philosophy\" and the slop ban list while respecting playbook structure for `ecommerce-home`.\n\n**No global-class catalog.** There is **no** `DESIGN_SYSTEM` block and **no** `<slug>.companion.json`. Every styled node gets its own entry under `styles` with `\"label\": \"local\"`, `variants[].props` as `{}`, and visual/layout CSS in `variants[].custom_css.raw` (base64). Consistency is your responsibility: repeat the same CSS literals where the design calls for identical treatment, or factor comments in `CSS_DRAFT` to keep pairs in sync.\n\n**Step 3 \u2014 HTML/CSS DRAFT (mandatory; inline only \u2014 never write draft files to disk)**\n\nAfter `DISCOVERY` + brief lines, emit a structural draft **in the assistant reply only** before any Elementor JSON.\n\nRequired emission shape \u2014 **three** labeled parts in order:\n\n1. **`HTML_DRAFT:`** then a ` ```html ` fence: semantic structure; every element that will be styled carries a `class` attribute whose tokens are **exactly** the style ids you will use as keys under `styles` on that V4 node (e.g. `class=\"local_hero_wrap\"` \u2192 `\"styles\": { \"local_hero_wrap\": { \u2026 } }`). One major block per playbook row / section.\n2. **`CSS_DRAFT:`** then a ` ```css ` fence: one rule per style id from the HTML (`#id` selectors forbidden). Each rule body is **declarations only** \u2014 the same text you will later base64-encode into `custom_css.raw` for the matching variant (desktop baseline unless you annotate otherwise).\n3. **`DRAFT_SELF_CHECK:`** then bullets: section order vs playbook; every HTML class has a CSS rule and a planned `styles` entry; slop / creativity gate (name one non-generic structural choice).\n\nDraft rules:\n\n- No inline `style=\"\"` in HTML.\n- Put **layout** in CSS (`display`, `flex-direction`, `align-items`, `justify-content`, `gap`, `flex-wrap`, \u2026) so the draft mirrors the V4 discipline: layout is **not** in `settings`.\n- **Do not** use `:hover`, `:focus`, `@media`, or nested selectors inside rule bodies \u2014 use **variants** (`meta.state`, `meta.breakpoint`) for those concerns in JSON (see \"Variants \u2014 responsive and state\").\n\n**Step 4 \u2014 Approval gate**\n\nIf the user did not explicitly allow proceeding without review, **stop after `DRAFT_SELF_CHECK`** and wait for approval. Do not emit JSON until approved (or go-ahead was in the brief).\n\n**Step 5 \u2014 Convert draft \u2192 element tree** \u2014 Map `HTML_DRAFT` to V4 nodes. For each `class` / style id on a node, create `styles[styleId]` with `\"label\": \"local\"`, `\"type\": \"class\"`, `variants` carrying `props: {}` and `custom_css: { \"raw\": \"<base64(UTF-8 CSS)>\" }` copied from the matching `CSS_DRAFT` rule. Set `settings.classes` to include that style id. Widget **settings** use only content keys + `link` etc. per the widget content key table \u2014 never put flex layout keys in `settings`.\n\n**Step 6 \u2014 Apply pattern recipes** for every non-trivial UI pattern (circle tile, promo strip, hero, search bar), translating prose into `custom_css` strings.\n\n**Step 7 \u2014 Validate, pre-handoff checklist, hand off to `validate-elementor-page`.** **Do not** emit companion JSON. Run `php validate-elementor-json.php <output.json>` from the workspace root; fix errors and re-run until clean. Then chain into `validate-elementor-page`.\n\n---\n\n## Canonical output shapes\n\n| `OUTPUT_TARGET` | Root shape | Container `elType` | Layout + visual styling live in | `settings` holds |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `db-inject` (default) | bare `[{\u2026}]` array | `\"e-flexbox\"` or `\"e-div-block\"` (no `widgetType`) | `styles[id].variants[*].custom_css.raw` (base64 CSS declarations); `variants[*].props` is always `{}` | `classes` ($$type: classes) + widget content keys |\n| `template-import` | envelope `{ version, title, type, page_settings, content: [\u2026] }` | same | same | same |\n\n**Hard rule:** For every `e-flexbox` / `e-div-block`, flex layout declarations (`display`, `flex-direction`, `align-items`, `justify-content`, `gap`, `flex-wrap`, \u2026) MUST appear inside `styles[localStyleId].variants[\u2026].custom_css` (as base64-encoded CSS text). They must NOT be placed in `settings`. `settings` holds `classes` and widget-specific content keys only.\n\nTemplate-import envelope:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"version\": \"0.4\",\n  \"title\":   \"Page \u2014 <name>\",\n  \"type\":    \"page\",\n  \"page_settings\": {},\n  \"content\": [ ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Widget content key table (canonical \u2014 no alternatives)\n\n| Widget | Content key in `settings` | `$$type` |\n|---|---|---|\n| `e-heading` | `title` | `html-v3` |\n| `e-paragraph` | `paragraph` | `html-v3` |\n| `e-button` | `text` | `html-v3` |\n| `e-image` | `image` | `image` (with nested `src` \u2192 `image-src` \u2192 `{ id, url }`) |\n| `e-tab` | `label` | `html-v3` |\n\n`html-v3` shape \u2014 **object**, not a plain string:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n  \"value\": {\n    \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Your text here</p>\" },\n    \"children\": []\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`image` shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"$$type\": \"image\",\n  \"value\": {\n    \"src\": {\n      \"$$type\": \"image-src\",\n      \"value\": {\n        \"id\": null,\n        \"url\": { \"$$type\": \"url\", \"value\": \"https://example.com/image.jpg\" }\n      }\n    },\n    \"size\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"full\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Link PropValue (`e-button`, `e-image`, `e-heading`, `e-paragraph`, `e-flexbox`, `e-div-block`)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"$$type\": \"link\",\n  \"value\": {\n    \"destination\":   { \"$$type\": \"url\",     \"value\": \"/signup\" },\n    \"isTargetBlank\": { \"$$type\": \"boolean\", \"value\": false }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nWrong: `{ \"$$type\": \"object\", \"value\": { \"url\": ... } }` \u2014 link silently drops.\n\n---\n\n## The V4 element tree \u2014 node shape\n\nEvery node in `content[]` (and recursively in `elements[]`) has:\n\n- `id` \u2014 stable string, unique within file.\n- `elType` \u2014 depends on element type (see table below). Never use one blanket value.\n- `widgetType` \u2014 **only** when `elType === \"widget\"`. Omit for containers.\n- `editor_settings` \u2014 `{ title: \"\u2026\" }`.\n- `settings` \u2014 PropValues for widget content + `classes`.\n- `styles` *(optional)* \u2014 local style definitions; **each variant uses `custom_css` for all paint/layout.**\n- `elements` *(optional)* \u2014 children.\n- `interactions` *(optional)* \u2014 `{ version: 1, items: [...] }`.\n\n### `elType` / `widgetType` rule \u2014 critical\n\n| Element | `elType` | `widgetType` |\n|---|---|---|\n| `e-heading` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-heading\"` |\n| `e-paragraph` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-paragraph\"` |\n| `e-button` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-button\"` |\n| `e-image` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-image\"` |\n| `e-svg` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-svg\"` |\n| `e-divider` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-divider\"` |\n| `e-youtube` | `\"widget\"` | `\"e-youtube\"` |\n| `e-flexbox` | `\"e-flexbox\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-div-block` | `\"e-div-block\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-tabs` | `\"e-tabs\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-tab` | `\"e-tab\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-tabs-menu` | `\"e-tabs-menu\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-tabs-content-area` | `\"e-tabs-content-area\"` | **omit** |\n| `e-tab-content` | `\"e-tab-content\"` | **omit** |\n\n**Never** `{ \"elType\": \"widget\", \"widgetType\": \"e-flexbox\" }`.\n\n### PropValues in `settings` only\n\nValues in **widget `settings`** (and interaction payloads) remain PropValues with `$$type` / `value` per widget schema. **Do not** put typed style PropValues in `styles[\u2026].variants[\u2026].props` \u2014 keep `props` as `{}` and express style in `custom_css`.\n\n### Styling model (this skill)\n\n1. Each styled element has one or more entries in its `styles` map (typically one local style id matching the draft class name).\n2. Each style definition: `\"label\": \"local\"`, `\"type\": \"class\"`, `\"id\": \"<same as key>\"`, `variants[]` each with `meta`, **`props`: `{}**, **`custom_css`: `{ \"raw\": \"<base64>\" }`** (or `null` if unused).\n3. `settings.classes.value` must list every style id applied to that node. Never `[]` when `styles` is non-empty.\n4. **Per-element `styles` map:** a style id referenced in `settings.classes` for a given node must be defined in **`that same node's** `styles` object**. To reuse the same CSS on another node, duplicate the style entry (same `custom_css.raw`) under a new id on that node \u2014 do not point at a sibling's style definition.\n\n### `custom_css` wire format (Elementor V4 atomic)\n\n- **Not** a PropValue \u2014 no `$$type` on `custom_css` itself.\n- Shape: `{ \"raw\": \"<base64-encoded UTF-8 CSS declarations>\" }`.\n- **Declarations only** inside the decoded string (no selectors). The engine wraps them as `.elementor .<cssName>{ \u2026 }`. Do **not** paste `selector { \u2026 }` or `{{WRAPPER}}` patterns from legacy V3.\n- **Pro:** feature `atomic-custom-css` is required for authoring/rendering in typical setups; without it, `custom_css` may be stripped. When `pro_active: false` in discovery, warn the user.\n- **Responsive / pseudo:** use additional variants with `meta.breakpoint` and `meta.state` \u2014 **not** `@media` or `:hover` inside the CSS string (Pro editor validation blocks many of those patterns).\n\n### Variants \u2014 responsive and state\n\nEach style definition is a list of variants with `meta: { breakpoint, state }`, `props: {}`, and `custom_css`. Only use breakpoint ids from `elementor://breakpoints/list`. For hover, use `meta.state: \"hover\"` (and rely on Elementor's selector wrapping \u2014 do not prefix declarations with `:hover`).\n\n### Container rules\n\nA widget is a container iff `llm_guidance.can_have_children === true`. Respect `allowed_child_types`, `allowed_parents`, and `required_direct_children`. For `e-tabs`, prefer the structure: `e-tabs \u2192 [e-tabs-menu \u2192 [e-tab \u2192 [e-paragraph]], e-tabs-content-area \u2192 [e-tab-content (settings.tab-id) \u2192 \u2026]]` (see failure modes).\n\n### Anchor snippet (custom_css + correct content keys)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"el_hero_heading\",\n  \"elType\": \"widget\",\n  \"widgetType\": \"e-heading\",\n  \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Hero Heading\" },\n  \"settings\": {\n    \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"e-hero-heading-css\"] },\n    \"title\": {\n      \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n      \"value\": {\n        \"content\":  { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<h1>Ship faster</h1>\" },\n        \"children\": []\n      }\n    },\n    \"tag\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"h1\" }\n  },\n  \"styles\": {\n    \"e-hero-heading-css\": {\n      \"id\": \"e-hero-heading-css\",\n      \"label\": \"local\",\n      \"type\": \"class\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n          \"props\": {},\n          \"custom_css\": {\n            \"raw\": \"Zm9udC1zaXplOiA0cmVtOyBsaW5lLWhlaWdodDogMS4yOyBjb2xvcjogIzE3MTMyMTs=\"\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n(`raw` decodes to `font-size: 4rem; line-height: 1.2; color: #171321;`)\n\n---\n\n## Page-type playbooks\n\n### `ecommerce-home`\n\n| # | Row purpose | Structure | Layout / CSS hints (in `custom_css`) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Utility strip | `e-flexbox` row, 3\u20136 `e-paragraph` / `e-button` | `display:flex; flex-direction:row; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center;` |\n| 2 | Header | `e-flexbox` row: logo `e-image`, search `e-flexbox`, icons | `justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:\u2026` |\n| 3 | Category nav | `e-flexbox` row, 6\u201310 `e-button` / `e-paragraph` | `flex-wrap:wrap; gap:\u2026` |\n| 4 | Icon grid | outer column \u2192 inner rows of tiles | `flex-wrap:wrap; justify-content:center;` on rows |\n| 5 | Hero band | row: `e-image` ~55% + column (h1, p, CTA) | `align-items:stretch; min-height:20rem;` on band |\n| 6 | Promo strip A | row of `e-div-block` tiles | `flex-wrap:nowrap; overflow-x:auto; gap:0.5rem;` |\n| 7 | Promo strip B | row, mixed tile widths | explicit `width` / `flex` per tile in CSS |\n| 8 | Footer bar | row: logo, links, copyright | `justify-content:space-between; align-items:center;` |\n\n### `landing` / `section-only`\n\nSame intent as the parent skill: sections earn their place; pick structural guidance from the closest playbook row when applicable.\n\n---\n\n## Pattern recipes\n\nTranslate each recipe into `custom_css.raw` on the relevant containers/widgets.\n\n- **Circle tile:** column flex, centered; image `width`/`height` + `border-radius:50%` in image node's CSS; caption small font.\n- **Promo strip:** row + nowrap + overflow-x; tiles `flex:0 0 auto; min-height:12rem; overflow:hidden;`.\n- **Hero band:** row, stretch; media `object-fit:cover` on image; column `gap` + padding on copy stack.\n- **Search bar:** row, border, radius; icon images fixed width `flex-shrink:0`.\n- **Logo:** always `e-image`, never `e-heading` as logo text.\n- **Icons:** prefer `e-icon` if discovery lists it; else small `e-image` SVG/PNG. No emoji as icons.\n\n---\n\n## Carousel / slider decision\n\nFetch `elementor://context/available-widgets/v4`. If carousel/slider exists, use it + schema. Else horizontal scroll strip + optional prev/next `e-button`s.\n\n---\n\n## RTL and locale\n\nWhen `LOCALE` is RTL (`he-IL`, `ar-*`, \u2026):\n\n1. Add to `page_settings` for template-import (or note for db-inject): `\"direction\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"rtl\" }`.\n2. Prefer **logical** CSS in `custom_css` (`text-align:end`, `padding-inline-*`, `margin-inline-*`, `align-items:flex-end` where appropriate).\n3. Hebrew copy in `html-v3` strings as needed.\n\n---\n\n## Fidelity budget\n\n**MUST:** playbook order, locale copy, one `e-image` per distinct visual, CTAs where shown, tile counts, footer when in playbook.\n\n**MAY:** motion details, pixel-perfect sizes, real brand assets (use Unsplash placeholders with non-empty URLs).\n\n**NEVER:** emoji icons, `e-heading` as logo, layout only in `settings`, empty image URLs, invented sections, huge default vertical gaps between ecommerce rows.\n\n---\n\n## Pre-handoff checklist\n\n- [ ] Bare `[{\u2026}]` unless user asked for template-import envelope\n- [ ] Correct `elType` / `widgetType` for every node\n- [ ] Every `e-flexbox` / `e-div-block` has flex layout in `custom_css`, not in `settings`\n- [ ] Text widgets: correct content keys + `html-v3` object shape\n- [ ] Every `styles[\u2026]` entry has `\"label\": \"local\"` exactly\n- [ ] Every variant has `\"props\": {}` and optional `custom_css` / `null`\n- [ ] Every `custom_css.raw` is valid base64 of UTF-8 **declarations only** (no `{`, no `@media`, no leading `:hover`)\n- [ ] Pseudo-states and breakpoints use `meta.state` / `meta.breakpoint` + separate variants \u2014 not embedded selectors in the string\n- [ ] Every node with `styles` lists all its style ids in `settings.classes.value`\n- [ ] `DISCOVERY` emitted; `discovery_gaps` explained or empty\n- [ ] `HTML_DRAFT` / `CSS_DRAFT` / `DRAFT_SELF_CHECK` emitted before JSON (unless brief waived); draft class names match `styles` keys\n- [ ] `e-image` / `link` / `image` shapes match SKILL examples\n- [ ] `page_settings.direction` for RTL when using template-import\n- [ ] Typography: proportional `line-height` in CSS; explicit `font-family` stack on text widgets via `custom_css`\n- [ ] Ghost buttons: readable contrast (solid `background` hex matching section + border + text color \u2014 not \"transparent\" keyword reliance)\n- [ ] Card rows: explicit widths or flex-basis so columns don't collapse to one per line unintentionally\n- [ ] Pro / `atomic-custom-css` warning if discovery says `pro_active: false`\n- [ ] `php validate-elementor-json.php <file.json>` passes\n\n---\n\n## Mode selection\n\n**Single-shot** \u2014 default for \u2264 8 sections.\n\n**Iterative** \u2014 large or ambiguous pages; still emit draft slices before JSON per slice.\n\n---\n\n## Interactions\n\nSame rules as parent skill: \u2264 3 per element; gate Pro triggers/effects/easings on `elementor://context/general`.\n\n---\n\n## Design philosophy\n\nApply `design-guidelines.md` and the slop ban / creativity gate from the parent skill's philosophy \u2014 but implement tokens as **literal CSS** inside `custom_css` (no global variable ids).\n\n---\n\n## On import errors\n\nFix the reported node only. Common: wrong `html-v3` / `link` / `image` shape; wrong `custom_css.raw` encoding; missing `label:\"local\"`; missing `classes` link; wrong `e-tabs` tree; invalid base64.\n\n---\n\n## Writing `custom_css` declarations\n\nAfter authoring human-readable CSS in `CSS_DRAFT`, encode each variant's declaration string as UTF-8 base64 into `raw`.\n\n**Examples of declaration strings:**\n\n```css\ndisplay:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:2rem;width:100%;max-width:72rem;\n```\n\n```css\nbackground:#5B3DF5;color:#ffffff;border-radius:999px;padding-block:0.875rem;padding-inline:1.5rem;\n```\n\n**Encoding helpers (run locally, paste output into JSON):**\n\n```bash\npython3 -c \"import base64; print(base64.b64encode(b'display:flex;').decode())\"\nnode -e \"console.log(Buffer.from('display:flex;','utf8').toString('base64'))\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Failure modes (high-frequency)\n\n- **`custom_css` wrong shape** \u2014 must be `{ \"raw\": \"<base64>\" }`, not a plain string \u2014 `Style_Parser` \u2192 `custom_css: invalid_type`.\n- **Invalid base64** \u2014 same error.\n- **Selectors / `@media` / leading `:hover` in the string** \u2014 breaks editor validation or produces invalid wrapped CSS; use variants instead.\n- **`custom_css` nested under `props`** \u2014 wrong; it is a sibling of `props` on the variant.\n- **Missing `\"label\": \"local\"`** on element `styles` entries \u2014 breaks local style recognition / save cycles.\n- **`settings.classes` empty** while `styles` exists \u2014 compiled CSS never attaches to DOM.\n- **Wrong `html-v3` / `link` / `image` / content keys** \u2014 same as parent skill.\n- **Wrong `elType` for containers** \u2014 silent empty output.\n- **Layout only in `settings`** \u2014 broken layout.\n- **`e-tabs` wrong DOM structure** \u2014 see parent skill failure mode; prefer flex stack if tabs are fragile on target version.\n- **Equal-width cards collapse** \u2014 add explicit `width`/`flex-basis` percents in `custom_css` on each card.\n- **Ghost button invisible** \u2014 set solid `background` hex + border + readable `color` in CSS.\n- **Pro license** \u2014 without `atomic-custom-css`, `custom_css` may be stripped \u2014 warn in handoff.\n\n---\n\n## See also\n\n- [design-guidelines.md](design-guidelines.md)\n- [reference.md](reference.md)\n- [examples.md](examples.md)\n- Parent skill for widget-only reference: `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/SKILL.md` (do **not** copy its typed-style or companion rules into generated JSON when this skill is active).\n";

export const referenceDocs = "# Reference \u2014 V4 page generation (custom_css skill)\n\nExpanded vocabulary, sample response shapes per resource, and the template-import envelope. **This skill does not use** `elementor://styles/schema/*`, `elementor://global-variables`, `elementor://global-classes`, or companion payloads \u2014 all layout and paint live in per-element `styles[\u2026].variants[\u2026].custom_css` (see `SKILL.md`).\n\n## Discovery output spec\n\nThe one-shot flow emits `DISCOVERY` before the brief / `HTML_DRAFT`. Resolve each topic in this order and record the winning source: MCP `elementor://...` resource, workspace dump at `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page-custom-css/discovery/<topic>.json`, wp-env probe, then skill-baked default. If a topic falls through to default, list it in `discovery_gaps`.\n\n**Topic `design_guidelines`:** read `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page-custom-css/design-guidelines.md` first; if missing, read `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/design-guidelines.md`; then `<workspace-root>/design-guidelines.md`; if none exist, use the brief\u2019s `DESIGN_GUIDELINES:` line and inline philosophy from `SKILL.md`.\n\n```yaml\nDISCOVERY:\n  source_resolution: { context: mcp|dump|probe|default, widgets: ..., breakpoints: ..., ... }\n  pro_active: true | false\n  elementor_version: \"0.4\"\n  breakpoints: [desktop, tablet, mobile]\n  widgets_available: [e-flexbox, e-div-block, e-heading, ...]\n  design_guidelines_source: inline | <path> | none\n  discovery_gaps: [topic names that fell through to skill-baked default; empty when every topic resolved]\n```\n\n**Default no-source example (current workspace pattern):**\n\n```yaml\nDISCOVERY:\n  source_resolution: { all: default }\n  pro_active: false\n  elementor_version: \"0.4\"\n  breakpoints: [desktop, tablet, mobile]\n  widgets_available: [e-flexbox, e-div-block, e-heading, e-paragraph, e-button, e-image, e-tabs, e-tab, e-tabs-menu, e-tabs-content-area, e-tab-content, e-svg, e-divider, e-youtube]\n  design_guidelines_source: .cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page-custom-css/design-guidelines.md\n  discovery_gaps: [context/general, widgets/available, breakpoints/list]\n```\n\n## Expanded vocabulary, by resource\n\nThese URIs describe the expected response shape. When no live source exposes them, treat the documented JSON as the data contract and supply it via a workspace dump under `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page-custom-css/discovery/` or fall back to skill-baked defaults.\n\n### `elementor://context/available-widgets/v4`\n\nLists every V4 (Atomic) widget registered on the site. Confirm a widget tag exists before emitting it.\n\n```json\n[\n  { \"type\": \"e-flexbox\",   \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Flex container\", \"is_container\": true },\n  { \"type\": \"e-div-block\", \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Block container\", \"is_container\": true },\n  { \"type\": \"e-heading\",   \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Heading\", \"is_container\": false },\n  { \"type\": \"e-paragraph\", \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Paragraph\", \"is_container\": false },\n  { \"type\": \"e-button\",    \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Button\",  \"is_container\": false },\n  { \"type\": \"e-image\",     \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Image\",   \"is_container\": false },\n  { \"type\": \"e-tabs\",      \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Tabs\",    \"is_container\": true },\n  { \"type\": \"e-tab\",       \"version\": \"v4\", \"description\": \"Tab item\",\"is_container\": true }\n]\n```\n\nIf a widget you want isn't here, ask the user; don't substitute silently.\n\n### `elementor://widgets/schema/{widgetType}`\n\nWidget's `settings` schema plus `llm_guidance`. Read before writing any `settings` block for a widget you haven't used yet in this session. **Do not** use `llm_guidance.default_styles` as typed `styles[\u2026].props` \u2014 translate intent into `custom_css` strings instead.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"title\": { \"kind\": \"union\", \"prop_types\": { \"string\": { \"kind\": \"string\" } } },\n    \"tag\":   { \"kind\": \"string\", \"settings\": { \"enum\": [\"h1\",\"h2\",\"h3\",\"h4\",\"h5\",\"h6\",\"p\",\"div\",\"span\"] } },\n    \"link\":  { \"kind\": \"object\", \"shape\": { \"url\": { \"kind\": \"string\" }, \"is_external\": { \"kind\": \"boolean\" } } }\n  },\n  \"description\": \"Heading widget\",\n  \"llm_guidance\": {\n    \"can_have_children\": false,\n    \"nesting\": { \"allowed_parents\": [\"e-flexbox\", \"e-div-block\"] }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nFor a container like `e-tabs`:\n\n```json\n\"llm_guidance\": {\n  \"can_have_children\": true,\n  \"nesting\": { \"allowed_child_types\": [\"e-tabs-menu\", \"e-tabs-content-area\"] },\n  \"required_direct_children\": [\"e-tabs-menu\", \"e-tabs-content-area\"]\n}\n```\n\n### `elementor://breakpoints/list`\n\nOnly enabled breakpoints. The full possible set is `widescreen`, `desktop`, `laptop`, `tablet_extra`, `tablet`, `mobile_extra`, `mobile` \u2014 but only ids in the response are valid in your output.\n\n```json\n[\n  { \"label\": \"Desktop\", \"constraint\": \"min\", \"value\": 1025 },\n  { \"label\": \"Tablet\",  \"constraint\": \"max\", \"value\": 1024 },\n  { \"label\": \"Mobile\",  \"constraint\": \"max\", \"value\": 767 }\n]\n```\n\nUse these ids in `variants[].meta.breakpoint` when splitting responsive `custom_css` across variants. **Do not** put `@media` queries inside the `custom_css` string \u2014 use one variant per breakpoint.\n\n### `elementor://interactions/schema`\n\nDiscriminated union of legal interaction shapes for this site, reflecting Free vs Pro.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"triggers\": [\"load\", \"scrollIn\"],\n  \"effects\":  [\"fade\", \"slide\", \"scale\"],\n  \"easings\":  [\"easeIn\"],\n  \"pro\": {\n    \"active\": false,\n    \"extra_triggers\": [\"hover\", \"click\", \"scrollOn\", \"scrollOut\"],\n    \"extra_effects\":  [\"custom\"],\n    \"extra_easings\":  [\"easeInOut\", \"easeOut\", \"backIn\", \"backInOut\", \"backOut\", \"linear\"]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### `elementor://context/general`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"timezone\": \"Asia/Jerusalem\",\n  \"postId\": 142,\n  \"currentPage\": { \"pageName\": \"Home\", \"pageTitle\": \"Home\", \"pageUrl\": \"/?post=142\" },\n  \"plugins\": { \"elementor-pro\": { \"active\": true, \"version\": \"3.x.y\" } }\n}\n```\n\nUse this for `postId` and to gate Pro-only emissions. **Atomic custom CSS** rendering in the editor/front typically requires Pro with license feature `atomic-custom-css`; treat `pro_active: false` as \"custom_css may be stripped on import/render\".\n\n## Wiring a discovery source\n\nFuture discovery sources should satisfy the data shapes above without changing `SKILL.md`. Add one of:\n\n1. MCP resources matching the `elementor://...` URIs.\n2. JSON dumps under `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page-custom-css/discovery/` using topic names like `breakpoints-list.json`, `widgets-available.json`, `context-general.json`.\n3. A wp-env probe invoked by `validator/` or `import.sh` that writes the same shapes.\n\n## Template-import envelope\n\nThe file the user imports \u2014 Elementor \u2192 Templates \u2192 Import \u2014 has this exact root shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"version\":       \"0.4\",\n  \"title\":         \"Landing \u2014 Acme Pricing\",\n  \"type\":          \"page\",\n  \"page_settings\": { },\n  \"content\":       [ ]\n}\n```\n\nField notes:\n\n- `version` \u2014 If the site exposes one through `elementor://context/general` use that; otherwise emit `\"0.4\"`.\n- `title` \u2014 Human and specific.\n- `type` \u2014 `\"page\"` | `\"section\"` | `\"container\"` per user intent.\n- `page_settings` \u2014 May include RTL `direction` PropValue for RTL locales (see `SKILL.md`).\n- `content` \u2014 array of root V4 element nodes.\n\nThe same shape is what Elementor produces on export.\n";

export const examplesDocs = "# Examples \u2014 V4 page generation (custom_css)\n\nAll styling uses `styles[id].variants[*].props: {}` and `variants[*].custom_css.raw` (base64 UTF-8 CSS **declarations only**). Widget **settings** use canonical content keys + `html-v3` / `image` / `link` PropValues per `SKILL.md`.\n\n## Encoding `custom_css.raw`\n\nDecode for sanity check:\n\n```bash\npython3 -c \"import base64; print(base64.b64decode('ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4Ow==').decode())\"\n```\n\nEncode a declaration string:\n\n```bash\npython3 -c \"import base64; s='display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;'; print(base64.b64encode(s.encode()).decode())\"\nnode -e \"console.log(Buffer.from('display:flex;','utf8').toString('base64'))\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Example 1 \u2014 Pricing section (db-inject, no companion)\n\n**Key rule:** every styled node has `\"label\": \"local\"` on each `styles[\u2026]` entry, `settings.classes` lists the style id(s), and each variant uses `props: {}` + `custom_css`.\n\nPrecomputed `raw` values (UTF-8 \u2192 base64):\n\n| Style id | Decoded CSS (abbrev.) | `raw` |\n|---|---|---|\n| `local_pricing_section` | `display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;padding-block:6rem;padding-inline:1.5rem;` | `ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOmNvbHVtbjthbGlnbi1pdGVtczpjZW50ZXI7cGFkZGluZy1ibG9jazo2cmVtO3BhZGRpbmctaW5saW5lOjEuNXJlbTs=` |\n| `local_pricing_content` | `display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:2rem;width:100%;max-width:72rem;` | `ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOmNvbHVtbjtnYXA6MnJlbTt3aWR0aDoxMDAlO21heC13aWR0aDo3MnJlbTs=` |\n| `local_pricing_heading` | `font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:750;line-height:1.2;color:#171321;` | `Zm9udC1zaXplOjIuNXJlbTtmb250LXdlaWdodDo3NTA7bGluZS1oZWlnaHQ6MS4yO2NvbG9yOiMxNzEzMjE7` |\n| `local_pricing_intro` | `font-size:1.125rem;line-height:1.7;color:#6F6A7C;` | `Zm9udC1zaXplOjEuMTI1cmVtO2xpbmUtaGVpZ2h0OjEuNztjb2xvcjojNkY2QTdDOw==` |\n| `local_pricing_cards_row` | `display:flex;flex-direction:row;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem;` | `ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOnJvdztmbGV4LXdyYXA6d3JhcDtnYXA6MXJlbTs=` |\n| `local_pricing_card` | `display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;background:#ffffff;border-radius:1.25rem;padding:1.5rem;width:30%;min-width:0;` | concat in real output \u2014 below uses one line |\n| `local_pricing_cta` | `background:#5B3DF5;color:#ffffff;border-radius:999px;padding-block:0.875rem;padding-inline:1.5rem;` | `YmFja2dyb3VuZDojNUIzREY1O2NvbG9yOiNmZmZmZmY7Ym9yZGVyLXJhZGl1czo5OTlweDtwYWRkaW5nLWJsb2NrOjAuODc1cmVtO3BhZGRpbmctaW5saW5lOjEuNXJlbTs=` |\n| `local_growth_title` | (same as heading) | same `raw` as `local_pricing_heading` |\n| `local_growth_copy` | (same as intro) | same `raw` as `local_pricing_intro` |\n\n> **Per-node local styles:** each element that lists a style id under `settings.classes` must ship a matching entry in its own `styles` map (duplicate the `variants` / `custom_css` when two nodes share the same look). Do not reference a style id defined only on a sibling.\n\nCard CSS single string used in JSON:\n\n`display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;background:#ffffff;border-radius:1.25rem;padding:1.5rem;width:30%;min-width:0;` \u2192 `ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOmNvbHVtbjtnYXA6MXJlbTtiYWNrZ3JvdW5kOiNmZmZmZmY7Ym9yZGVyLXJhZGl1czoxLjI1cmVtO3BhZGRpbmc6MS41cmVtO3dpZHRoOjMwJTttaW4td2lkdGg6MDs=`\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"id\": \"el_pricing_section\",\n    \"elType\": \"e-flexbox\",\n    \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Section\" },\n    \"settings\": {\n      \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_pricing_section\"] }\n    },\n    \"styles\": {\n      \"local_pricing_section\": {\n        \"id\": \"local_pricing_section\",\n        \"label\": \"local\",\n        \"type\": \"class\",\n        \"variants\": [\n          {\n            \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n            \"props\": {},\n            \"custom_css\": {\n              \"raw\": \"ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOmNvbHVtbjthbGlnbi1pdGVtczpjZW50ZXI7cGFkZGluZy1ibG9jazo2cmVtO3BhZGRpbmctaW5saW5lOjEuNXJlbTs=\"\n            }\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    },\n    \"elements\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"el_pricing_content\",\n        \"elType\": \"e-flexbox\",\n        \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Content\" },\n        \"settings\": {\n          \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_pricing_content\"] }\n        },\n        \"styles\": {\n          \"local_pricing_content\": {\n            \"id\": \"local_pricing_content\",\n            \"label\": \"local\",\n            \"type\": \"class\",\n            \"variants\": [\n              {\n                \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                \"props\": {},\n                \"custom_css\": {\n                  \"raw\": \"ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOmNvbHVtbjtnYXA6MnJlbTt3aWR0aDoxMDAlO21heC13aWR0aDo3MnJlbTs=\"\n                }\n              }\n            ]\n          }\n        },\n        \"elements\": [\n          {\n            \"id\": \"el_pricing_heading\",\n            \"elType\": \"widget\",\n            \"widgetType\": \"e-heading\",\n            \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Heading\" },\n            \"settings\": {\n              \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_pricing_heading\"] },\n              \"title\": {\n                \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n                \"value\": {\n                  \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<h2>Plans that scale with you</h2>\" },\n                  \"children\": []\n                }\n              },\n              \"tag\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"h2\" }\n            },\n            \"styles\": {\n              \"local_pricing_heading\": {\n                \"id\": \"local_pricing_heading\",\n                \"label\": \"local\",\n                \"type\": \"class\",\n                \"variants\": [\n                  {\n                    \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                    \"props\": {},\n                    \"custom_css\": {\n                      \"raw\": \"Zm9udC1zaXplOjIuNXJlbTtmb250LXdlaWdodDo3NTA7bGluZS1oZWlnaHQ6MS4yO2NvbG9yOiMxNzEzMjE7\"\n                    }\n                  }\n                ]\n              }\n            }\n          },\n          {\n            \"id\": \"el_pricing_intro\",\n            \"elType\": \"widget\",\n            \"widgetType\": \"e-paragraph\",\n            \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Intro\" },\n            \"settings\": {\n              \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_pricing_intro\"] },\n              \"paragraph\": {\n                \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n                \"value\": {\n                  \"content\": {\n                    \"$$type\": \"string\",\n                    \"value\": \"<p>Start small, then add seats and workflows when your team grows.</p>\"\n                  },\n                  \"children\": []\n                }\n              }\n            },\n            \"styles\": {\n              \"local_pricing_intro\": {\n                \"id\": \"local_pricing_intro\",\n                \"label\": \"local\",\n                \"type\": \"class\",\n                \"variants\": [\n                  {\n                    \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                    \"props\": {},\n                    \"custom_css\": {\n                      \"raw\": \"Zm9udC1zaXplOjEuMTI1cmVtO2xpbmUtaGVpZ2h0OjEuNztjb2xvcjojNkY2QTdDOw==\"\n                    }\n                  }\n                ]\n              }\n            }\n          },\n          {\n            \"id\": \"el_pricing_cards\",\n            \"elType\": \"e-flexbox\",\n            \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Cards\" },\n            \"settings\": {\n              \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_pricing_cards_row\"] }\n            },\n            \"styles\": {\n              \"local_pricing_cards_row\": {\n                \"id\": \"local_pricing_cards_row\",\n                \"label\": \"local\",\n                \"type\": \"class\",\n                \"variants\": [\n                  {\n                    \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                    \"props\": {},\n                    \"custom_css\": {\n                      \"raw\": \"ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOnJvdztmbGV4LXdyYXA6d3JhcDtnYXA6MXJlbTs=\"\n                    }\n                  }\n                ]\n              }\n            },\n            \"elements\": [\n              {\n                \"id\": \"el_pricing_card_growth\",\n                \"elType\": \"e-div-block\",\n                \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Growth Plan\" },\n                \"settings\": {\n                  \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_pricing_card\"] }\n                },\n                \"styles\": {\n                  \"local_pricing_card\": {\n                    \"id\": \"local_pricing_card\",\n                    \"label\": \"local\",\n                    \"type\": \"class\",\n                    \"variants\": [\n                      {\n                        \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                        \"props\": {},\n                        \"custom_css\": {\n                          \"raw\": \"ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOmNvbHVtbjtnYXA6MXJlbTtiYWNrZ3JvdW5kOiNmZmZmZmY7Ym9yZGVyLXJhZGl1czoxLjI1cmVtO3BhZGRpbmc6MS41cmVtO3dpZHRoOjMwJTttaW4td2lkdGg6MDs=\"\n                        }\n                      }\n                    ]\n                  }\n                },\n                \"elements\": [\n                  {\n                    \"id\": \"el_growth_title\",\n                    \"elType\": \"widget\",\n                    \"widgetType\": \"e-heading\",\n                    \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Growth Title\" },\n                    \"settings\": {\n                      \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_growth_title\"] },\n                      \"title\": {\n                        \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n                        \"value\": {\n                          \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<h3>Growth</h3>\" },\n                          \"children\": []\n                        }\n                      },\n                      \"tag\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"h3\" }\n                    },\n                    \"styles\": {\n                      \"local_growth_title\": {\n                        \"id\": \"local_growth_title\",\n                        \"label\": \"local\",\n                        \"type\": \"class\",\n                        \"variants\": [\n                          {\n                            \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                            \"props\": {},\n                            \"custom_css\": {\n                              \"raw\": \"Zm9udC1zaXplOjIuNXJlbTtmb250LXdlaWdodDo3NTA7bGluZS1oZWlnaHQ6MS4yO2NvbG9yOiMxNzEzMjE7\"\n                            }\n                          }\n                        ]\n                      }\n                    }\n                  },\n                  {\n                    \"id\": \"el_growth_copy\",\n                    \"elType\": \"widget\",\n                    \"widgetType\": \"e-paragraph\",\n                    \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Growth Copy\" },\n                    \"settings\": {\n                      \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_growth_copy\"] },\n                      \"paragraph\": {\n                        \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n                        \"value\": {\n                          \"content\": {\n                            \"$$type\": \"string\",\n                            \"value\": \"<p>For teams building repeatable launch motions.</p>\"\n                          },\n                          \"children\": []\n                        }\n                      }\n                    },\n                    \"styles\": {\n                      \"local_growth_copy\": {\n                        \"id\": \"local_growth_copy\",\n                        \"label\": \"local\",\n                        \"type\": \"class\",\n                        \"variants\": [\n                          {\n                            \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                            \"props\": {},\n                            \"custom_css\": {\n                              \"raw\": \"Zm9udC1zaXplOjEuMTI1cmVtO2xpbmUtaGVpZ2h0OjEuNztjb2xvcjojNkY2QTdDOw==\"\n                            }\n                          }\n                        ]\n                      }\n                    }\n                  },\n                  {\n                    \"id\": \"el_growth_cta\",\n                    \"elType\": \"widget\",\n                    \"widgetType\": \"e-button\",\n                    \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Growth CTA\" },\n                    \"settings\": {\n                      \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_growth_cta\"] },\n                      \"text\": {\n                        \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n                        \"value\": {\n                          \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Start Growth</p>\" },\n                          \"children\": []\n                        }\n                      }\n                    },\n                    \"styles\": {\n                      \"local_growth_cta\": {\n                        \"id\": \"local_growth_cta\",\n                        \"label\": \"local\",\n                        \"type\": \"class\",\n                        \"variants\": [\n                          {\n                            \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                            \"props\": {},\n                            \"custom_css\": {\n                              \"raw\": \"YmFja2dyb3VuZDojNUIzREY1O2NvbG9yOiNmZmZmZmY7Ym9yZGVyLXJhZGl1czo5OTlweDtwYWRkaW5nLWJsb2NrOjAuODc1cmVtO3BhZGRpbmctaW5saW5lOjEuNXJlbTs=\"\n                            }\n                          }\n                        ]\n                      }\n                    }\n                  }\n                ]\n              }\n            ]\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Example 2 \u2014 `e-tabs` with required shell (custom_css on wrappers)\n\nUse `e-tabs \u2192 e-tabs-menu (e-tab \u2192 e-paragraph label) + e-tabs-content-area (e-tab-content + panel body)`. Each `e-tab` needs an `id`; each `e-tab-content` sets `tab-id` to that id.\n\n`local_tabs_shell` = `display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.75rem;` \u2192 `ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOmNvbHVtbjtnYXA6MC43NXJlbTs=`\n\n`local_tab_label` = `text-align:center;` \u2192 `dGV4dC1hbGlnbjpjZW50ZXI7`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"el_tabs_root\",\n  \"elType\": \"e-tabs\",\n  \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Feature Tabs\" },\n  \"settings\": {\n    \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_tabs_shell\"] }\n  },\n  \"styles\": {\n    \"local_tabs_shell\": {\n      \"id\": \"local_tabs_shell\",\n      \"label\": \"local\",\n      \"type\": \"class\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n          \"props\": {},\n          \"custom_css\": { \"raw\": \"ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOmNvbHVtbjtnYXA6MC43NXJlbTs=\" }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  },\n  \"elements\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"el_tabs_menu\",\n      \"elType\": \"e-tabs-menu\",\n      \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Tabs Menu\" },\n      \"settings\": {},\n      \"elements\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"el_tab_a\",\n          \"elType\": \"e-tab\",\n          \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Tab A\" },\n          \"settings\": {\n            \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_tab_label\"] }\n          },\n          \"styles\": {\n            \"local_tab_label\": {\n              \"id\": \"local_tab_label\",\n              \"label\": \"local\",\n              \"type\": \"class\",\n              \"variants\": [\n                {\n                  \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                  \"props\": {},\n                  \"custom_css\": { \"raw\": \"dGV4dC1hbGlnbjpjZW50ZXI7\" }\n                }\n              ]\n            }\n          },\n          \"elements\": [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"el_tab_a_label\",\n              \"elType\": \"widget\",\n              \"widgetType\": \"e-paragraph\",\n              \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Tab A label\" },\n              \"settings\": {\n                \"paragraph\": {\n                  \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n                  \"value\": {\n                    \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Performance</p>\" },\n                    \"children\": []\n                  }\n                }\n              }\n            }\n          ]\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"el_tabs_panels\",\n      \"elType\": \"e-tabs-content-area\",\n      \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Tabs Panels\" },\n      \"settings\": {},\n      \"elements\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"el_tab_panel_a\",\n          \"elType\": \"e-tab-content\",\n          \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Panel A\" },\n          \"settings\": {\n            \"tab-id\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"el_tab_a\" }\n          },\n          \"elements\": [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"el_tab_a_body\",\n              \"elType\": \"widget\",\n              \"widgetType\": \"e-paragraph\",\n              \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Panel A body\" },\n              \"settings\": {\n                \"paragraph\": {\n                  \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n                  \"value\": {\n                    \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Sub-50ms TTFB.</p>\" },\n                    \"children\": []\n                  }\n                }\n              }\n            }\n          ]\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n> Trim duplicate `styles` maps if the same `local_tab_label` id is reused on multiple nodes \u2014 **each style id should appear once in the tree** or use distinct ids per node. The snippet above shows the pattern; prefer unique style ids per node to avoid JSON merge collisions on import.\n\n---\n\n## Example 3 \u2014 One local style, mobile padding + desktop hover variants\n\n`mobile_pad` \u2192 `cGFkZGluZzoxLjVyZW07`\n\n`hover_lift` \u2192 `dHJhbnNmb3JtOnRyYW5zbGF0ZVkoLTRweCk7Ym94LXNoYWRvdzowIDMwcHggNjBweCByZ2JhKDE1LDExOCwxMTAsMC4xOCk7`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"el_pricing_card\",\n  \"elType\": \"e-div-block\",\n  \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Pricing Card\" },\n  \"settings\": {\n    \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_card_surface\"] }\n  },\n  \"styles\": {\n    \"local_card_surface\": {\n      \"id\": \"local_card_surface\",\n      \"label\": \"local\",\n      \"type\": \"class\",\n      \"variants\": [\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"mobile\", \"state\": null },\n          \"props\": {},\n          \"custom_css\": { \"raw\": \"cGFkZGluZzoxLjVyZW07\" }\n        },\n        {\n          \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": \"hover\" },\n          \"props\": {},\n          \"custom_css\": {\n            \"raw\": \"dHJhbnNmb3JtOnRyYW5zbGF0ZVkoLTRweCk7Ym94LXNoYWRvdzowIDMwcHggNjBweCByZ2JhKDE1LDExOCwxMTAsMC4xOCk7\"\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nDo **not** write `:hover { \u2026 }` inside `raw` \u2014 use `meta.state: \"hover\"` as above.\n\n---\n\n## Example 4 \u2014 Importable `section` template (CTA band)\n\n`local_cta_root` uses the precomputed `cta_root` string:\n\n`ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOmNvbHVtbjthbGlnbi1pdGVtczpjZW50ZXI7anVzdGlmeS1jb250ZW50OmNlbnRlcjtnYXA6MS41cmVtO3BhZGRpbmctYmxvY2s6OHJlbTtwYWRkaW5nLWlubGluZToycmVtOw==`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"version\": \"0.4\",\n  \"title\": \"CTA Section \u2014 Trial Signup\",\n  \"type\": \"section\",\n  \"page_settings\": {},\n  \"content\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"el_cta_root\",\n      \"elType\": \"e-flexbox\",\n      \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"CTA Section\" },\n      \"settings\": {\n        \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_cta_root\"] }\n      },\n      \"styles\": {\n        \"local_cta_root\": {\n          \"id\": \"local_cta_root\",\n          \"label\": \"local\",\n          \"type\": \"class\",\n          \"variants\": [\n            {\n              \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n              \"props\": {},\n              \"custom_css\": {\n                \"raw\": \"ZGlzcGxheTpmbGV4O2ZsZXgtZGlyZWN0aW9uOmNvbHVtbjthbGlnbi1pdGVtczpjZW50ZXI7anVzdGlmeS1jb250ZW50OmNlbnRlcjtnYXA6MS41cmVtO3BhZGRpbmctYmxvY2s6OHJlbTtwYWRkaW5nLWlubGluZToycmVtOw==\"\n              }\n            }\n          ]\n        }\n      },\n      \"elements\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"el_cta_heading\",\n          \"elType\": \"widget\",\n          \"widgetType\": \"e-heading\",\n          \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"CTA Heading\" },\n          \"settings\": {\n            \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_cta_heading\"] },\n            \"title\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n              \"value\": {\n                \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<h2>Ready when you are.</h2>\" },\n                \"children\": []\n              }\n            },\n            \"tag\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"h2\" }\n          },\n          \"styles\": {\n            \"local_cta_heading\": {\n              \"id\": \"local_cta_heading\",\n              \"label\": \"local\",\n              \"type\": \"class\",\n              \"variants\": [\n                {\n                  \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                  \"props\": {},\n                  \"custom_css\": {\n                    \"raw\": \"Zm9udC1zaXplOjIuNXJlbTtmb250LXdlaWdodDo3NTA7bGluZS1oZWlnaHQ6MS4yO2NvbG9yOiMxNzEzMjE7\"\n                  }\n                }\n              ]\n            }\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"el_cta_sub\",\n          \"elType\": \"widget\",\n          \"widgetType\": \"e-paragraph\",\n          \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"CTA Subhead\" },\n          \"settings\": {\n            \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_cta_sub\"] },\n            \"paragraph\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n              \"value\": {\n                \"content\": {\n                  \"$$type\": \"string\",\n                  \"value\": \"<p>Spin up a project in under 60 seconds. No credit card.</p>\"\n                },\n                \"children\": []\n              }\n            }\n          },\n          \"styles\": {\n            \"local_cta_sub\": {\n              \"id\": \"local_cta_sub\",\n              \"label\": \"local\",\n              \"type\": \"class\",\n              \"variants\": [\n                {\n                  \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                  \"props\": {},\n                  \"custom_css\": {\n                    \"raw\": \"Zm9udC1zaXplOjEuMTI1cmVtO2xpbmUtaGVpZ2h0OjEuNztjb2xvcjojNkY2QTdDOw==\"\n                  }\n                }\n              ]\n            }\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"el_cta_button\",\n          \"elType\": \"widget\",\n          \"widgetType\": \"e-button\",\n          \"editor_settings\": { \"title\": \"Primary CTA\" },\n          \"settings\": {\n            \"classes\": { \"$$type\": \"classes\", \"value\": [\"local_cta_button\"] },\n            \"text\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"html-v3\",\n              \"value\": {\n                \"content\": { \"$$type\": \"string\", \"value\": \"<p>Start free trial</p>\" },\n                \"children\": []\n              }\n            },\n            \"link\": {\n              \"$$type\": \"link\",\n              \"value\": {\n                \"destination\": { \"$$type\": \"url\", \"value\": \"/signup\" },\n                \"isTargetBlank\": { \"$$type\": \"boolean\", \"value\": false }\n              }\n            }\n          },\n          \"styles\": {\n            \"local_cta_button\": {\n              \"id\": \"local_cta_button\",\n              \"label\": \"local\",\n              \"type\": \"class\",\n              \"variants\": [\n                {\n                  \"meta\": { \"breakpoint\": \"desktop\", \"state\": null },\n                  \"props\": {},\n                  \"custom_css\": {\n                    \"raw\": \"YmFja2dyb3VuZDojNUIzREY1O2NvbG9yOiNmZmZmZmY7Ym9yZGVyLXJhZGl1czo5OTlweDtwYWRkaW5nLWJsb2NrOjAuODc1cmVtO3BhZGRpbmctaW5saW5lOjEuNXJlbTs=\"\n                  }\n                }\n              ]\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThis template ships **no** global primitives \u2014 only local `styles` + `custom_css`.\n";

export const designGuidelinesDocs = "# Design guidelines \u2014 Elementor V4 JSON generation\n\nPrescriptive rules for **authoring** template JSON (global variables, global classes, `styles` props, copy, structure). Validators use `validate-elementor-page/visual-rubric.md` for screenshot scoring; keep generation guidance here so skills stay separated.\n\n## Philosophy\n\nBuild **distinctive, high-fidelity** layouts \u2014 not anonymous wireframes. Every page should read as a deliberate product: intentional color, typography hierarchy, and section rhythm. Aim for polished UI, not default browser chrome.\n\n### User specification is law\n\nWhen the brief names **hex colors**, **fonts**, **section order**, **copy**, **locale/RTL**, or references a **screenshot/URL**, those choices override convenience defaults. Encode them in variables, classes, and widget content exactly. Output that ignores an explicit user constraint is wrong.\n\nWhen the user gives **no** visual spec, you still owe a cohesive system: derive a small palette, type scale, and spacing rhythm from `PAGE_TYPE`, `BRAND_COLORS` (if any), and `SECTIONS`.\n\n---\n\n## Bold direction (commit before you branch the tree)\n\nAnswer briefly (internally or in notes to yourself):\n\n1. **Purpose & audience** \u2014 Who lands here and what should they do?\n2. **Tone** \u2014 Pick and hold one direction (e.g. editorial, brutalist/minimal, soft retail, luxury restraint, playful, utilitarian). Intensity is optional; **intentionality** is not.\n3. **Differentiation** \u2014 What one thing should this page be remembered for? (Asymmetry, typographic drama, a single strong accent, unusual section order, etc.)\n\nThen execute that direction in **JSON only**: variables, class props, flex layout, imagery choices, and real copy \u2014 not generic placeholders.\n\n---\n\n## Typography (Elementor-native)\n\n- Encode **`font-family`** (and weight/size/line-height) in **global classes** or local `styles[\u2026].variants[\u2026].props` using valid PropValue shapes from the style schema.\n- Prefer **two roles**: a display / heading treatment and a body treatment. Use **large weight contrast** between hero headline and body (e.g. 700 vs 400; size ratio 3\u00d7+ when the brief allows).\n- **Avoid defaulting every project** to the same \u201csafe\u201d pairing (e.g. Inter + Inter) when the brief is open \u2014 pick stacks that match the tone: distinctive webfonts, or a deliberate **system UI** stack (`system-ui`, `-apple-system`, `Segoe UI`, sans-serif) for crisp product UI.\n- **Line-height** must stay proportional to font-size (see `SKILL.md` pre-handoff checklist). Never use absolute line-heights smaller than the font size on headings.\n\n---\n\n## Color & theme\n\n- Prefer **one dominant** brand/adjacent color, **one accent**, and **tinted neutrals** \u2014 not five accents at equal weight.\n- Express colors as **`global-color-variable`** entries in the companion payload when they repeat; reference by id in props.\n- **Purple\u2013blue gradients on white** are a known generic pattern \u2014 use only when the brief or brand demands purple.\n- Tint neutrals toward warm or cool to match the palette; flat `#f5f5f5` / `#333` with zero temperature reads as unfinished.\n\n---\n\n## Motion\n\n- Use **`interactions`** sparingly (see `SKILL.md`): 2\u20133 high-impact moments (hero reveal, primary CTA, one featured block). Respect Pro vs free triggers.\n- Prefer **one orchestrated** load/stagger story over scattered micro-motion on every widget.\n\n---\n\n## Spatial composition\n\n- Prefer **asymmetry**, mixed column ratios, overlap, or broken grids over \u201chero centered + three equal cards\u201d when the playbook allows.\n- Vary **section vertical rhythm** \u2014 not identical `padding-block` on every section unless the brief is a strict system.\n- Respect **`layout-in-styles`**: flex lives in `styles[\u2026].props`, not only in `settings`.\n\n---\n\n## Backgrounds & depth\n\n- Alternate section surfaces (subtle tints, thin borders, restrained shadow) so the page is not one flat `#fff` field.\n- Use **`background`** PropValue (schema-shaped), gradients, or images where they support the tone \u2014 not decorative noise unrelated to content.\n- Cards and tiles: controlled **`border-radius`** and **box-shadow** from the catalog (`card-surface`, etc.) unless the brief demands sharp flat UI.\n\n---\n\n## Copy & content\n\n- **No vague hype** (\u201cRevolutionize your workflow\u201d) unless the brief uses that voice. Prefer concrete outcomes, numbers, and product truth.\n- **No Elementor default strings** in shipped trees (`This is a title`, `Type your paragraph here`, `Click here`).\n\n---\n\n## JSON-level anti-slop (clich\u00e9s to avoid in structure and tokens)\n\nWhen the brief does not explicitly require these patterns, avoid:\n\n- **Three-up feature grid** as the only layout idea (icon \u2192 title \u2192 blurb \u00d73, repeated identically).\n- **Perfect symmetry everywhere** (image left / text right / repeat forever).\n- **Identical card heights and radii** on every surface \u2014 vary featured vs compact where it helps hierarchy.\n- **Emoji as icons** \u2014 use `e-image` / SVG or `e-icon` when available per discovery.\n- **Trusted-by logo bar** immediately under the hero without brief support.\n- **Magic dust** decor (random floating shapes) with no brand or content rationale.\n- **Rounded corners identical on every control** \u2014 mix radii intentionally (pills vs sharp vs one soft family).\n\nThese are **authoring** rules. The validator\u2019s **`visual-rubric.md`** adds screenshot-specific failure lines (e.g. visible \u201cAI template\u201d tells).\n\n---\n\n## Consistency with `validate-elementor-page`\n\nGenerators should satisfy both this file and the visual rubric. If you choose **system UI** stacks, set them **explicitly** in styles so the front does not fall back to browser default serif. If you choose **webfonts**, set `font-family` to real stack strings the engine can resolve (Google/font CDN is a site concern \u2014 still emit the intended `font-family` names in JSON).\n\n---\n\n## Resolution\n\nAgents read this file for discovery topic `design_guidelines` in this order:\n\n1. `.cursor/skills/generate-elementor-page/design-guidelines.md` (this file)\n2. `<workspace-root>/design-guidelines.md` if (1) is missing\n\nIf neither exists, use inline brief + `SKILL.md` / `reference.md` defaults.\n";
